                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/3622a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-06T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. For the Secretary of State:</p>
                <p>Before you left Washington, you discussed with the President a declaration by him
                    of the attitude of this Government towards the Bolshevik authorities in Russia,
                    and found that the President preferred to withhold any separate statement by
                    himself until he could discuss the matter with the leaders of the Associated
                    Governments. The reports we receive and which are repeated to you by our
                    Embassies and Legations, show the growing menace of Bolshevism outside of
                    Russia. I believe no one can take the lead so well as the President in defining
                    the attitude of the Associated Governments on this question and would be glad to
                    know what steps, if any, in that direction have been taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
